instruction:
Let the function $f$, with period $2\pi$, be the periodic extension of the function $e^{\alpha x}$ defined on $[0, 2\pi)$, where $\alpha$ is any given non-zero real number. What is the trigonometric Fourier series of $f$?

Options:
A. $$
\frac{e^{3 \pi\alpha}+1} {e^{\pi\alpha}-1}
$$
B. $$
\frac{e^{3 \pi\alpha}-1} {e^{\alpha}+1}
$$
C. $$
\frac{e^{2 \alpha \pi}+1} {2}
$$
D. $$
\frac{e^{2 \pi\alpha}+1} {e^{2 \pi\alpha}-1}
$$
E. $$
\frac{1+e^{2 \pi\alpha}} {1-e^{2 \pi\alpha}}
$$
F. $$
\frac{e^{4 \pi\alpha}-1} {e^{\alpha}+1}
$$
G. $$
\frac{e^{2 \pi\alpha}-1} {e^{2 \pi\alpha}+1}
$$
H. $$
\frac{e^{2 \pi\alpha}+2} {e^{2 \pi\alpha}-2}
$$
I. $$
\frac{e^{\alpha}+e^{-\alpha}} {2}
$$
J. $$
\frac{e^{\pi\alpha}+e^{-\pi\alpha}} {1}
$$
